<p><b>Critical notes.</b> The headline real-robot result is encouraging, but the evaluation is narrow: three tabletop tasks on one UR3 setup. The simulation comparison with π₀.5 is not data-matched, which the authors acknowledge. More importantly, the project page lists the code as “Coming soon,” so the TraceExtract pipeline and the action-expert checkpoint cannot be inspected or reproduced yet. The method reconstruction above is based on the paper and appendix; the real implementation details remain unverified.</p>

<hr/>

<h1>Theme 2 — Full-Stack Action-Labeled VLAs</h1>

<p>At the other pole, several groups are treating the robot-learning problem as a systems problem: co-design data collection hardware, model architecture, training recipe, and deployment stack. The strongest new entry is Tencent's HyVLA-0.5.</p>

