<p><b>Bottom line.</b> HyVLA-0.5 is a serious, well-engineered training and inference baseline, and the released model achieves the reported RoboTwin numbers. But the paper's strongest claims — near-ceiling real-robot performance after FlowPRO and smooth high-frequency deployment — depend on components that are not yet public. Treat it as a strong open VLA recipe, not a complete real-world deployment stack.</p>

<hr/>

